You're most likely missing the **`BindingContext`** assignment. The `{Binding}` markup extension needs a source object to bind against.

**Fix — set `BindingContext` in code-behind:**

```csharp
public partial class MyPage : ContentPage
{
    public MyPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = new MyViewModel();
    }
}
```

**Or set it in XAML:**

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels"
             ...>
    <ContentPage.BindingContext>
        <vm:MyViewModel />
    </ContentPage.BindingContext>
    ...
</ContentPage>
```

**Also ensure** your ViewModel raises `PropertyChanged` (or uses `[ObservableProperty]` from the MVVM Community Toolkit) so the UI updates when values change:

```csharp
public partial class MyViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string title;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private string description;
}
```

**TL;DR:** No `BindingContext` → bindings resolve to `null` → blank labels.
